- what it is
- what it requires
- how you knew about this job
- explain why it's useful to society

I’d like to talk about a job that is very useful to society, which is being a sewer worker.

Their main responsibility is to maintain and clean underground sewage systems to make sure everything works properly. This includes clearing blockages, repairing damaged pipes, and checking for any problems in the system. The job requires physical strength and endurance, as they often have to work in narrow and dirty environments. It can also be quite challenging because they have to deal with unpleasant smells and sometimes risky conditions.

I first learned more about this job a few years ago when I watched a video on social media showing a typical working day of a sewer worker. I was quite surprised by how tough the job was, and it made me appreciate their work more.

In my opinion, this job is extremely important because it helps protect public health and keeps the environment clean. Without sewer workers, waste would build up quickly, which could lead to pollution and even the spread of diseases.

Overall, although this job is not very visible, I believe it plays a vital role in society and deserves more respect.
